<p>This article is, IMHO, an example of how you can almost always prove any point you want to prove with statistics, providing you slice the data the right way.</p>
<p>Focusing on the very poor (bottom 20%) and on income rather than wealth, the statistics do come out the way the author of this article demonstrates.</p>
